<p>We used a two-age group model (
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="i92">
   <mo>&lt;</mo>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>60-y-olds and 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="i93">
   <mo>≥</mo>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>60-y-olds) to demonstrate an optimal social distancing strategy while shielding 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="i94">
   <mo>≥</mo>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>60-y-old individuals. To preserve the data-informed contact structure, we made the approximation that the age-specific incidence was constant for age groups 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="i95">
   <mo>&lt;</mo>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>60 y and similarly for 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="i96">
   <mo>≥</mo>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>60 y. The two-age group contact matrix is then given by a weighted sum of the POLYMOD-derived contact matrix, 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="i97">
   <msubsup>
    <mrow>
     <mi>c</mi>
    </mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mi>a</mi>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <mi>b</mi>
    </mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mn>2</mn>
      </mrow>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
   </msubsup>
   <mo>=</mo>
   <msub>
    <mrow>
     <mo>∑</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mi>i</mi>
     <mo>∈</mo>
     <mi>a</mi>
    </mrow>
   </msub>
   <msub>
    <mrow>
     <mo>∑</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mi>j</mi>
     <mo>∈</mo>
     <mi>b</mi>
    </mrow>
   </msub>
   <mrow>
    <mo>(</mo>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mrow>
       <mi>N</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
       <mi>i</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mo>/</mo>
     <msub>
      <mrow>
       <mi>N</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
       <mi>b</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
    <mo>)</mo>
   </mrow>
   <msub>
    <mrow>
     <mi>c</mi>
    </mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mi>i</mi>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <mi>j</mi>
    </mrow>
   </msub>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>, where 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="i98">
   <mi>a</mi>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> and 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="i99">
   <mi>b</mi>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> index age groups 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="i100">
   <mrow>
    <mo>{</mo>
    <mrow>
     <mo>&lt;</mo>
     <mn>60</mn>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <mo>≥</mo>
     <mn>60</mn>
    </mrow>
    <mo>}</mo>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>. Aside from the contact matrix, the model is identical in structure to that given in 
 <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="eq1">Eqs. 
  <bold>1</bold>
 </xref>–
 <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="eq6">
  <bold>6</bold>
 </xref>.
</p>
